00:03:00.520 --> 00:03:03.780
may have a big impact to understand why

71
00:03:03.780 --> 00:03:06.240
let's return to the differences between classical

72
00:03:06.240 --> 00:03:08.340
and quantum computing just

73
00:03:08.340 --> 00:03:11.360
as classical computers use bits of information

74
00:03:11.360 --> 00:03:13.759
quantum computers use cubits

75
00:03:13.760 --> 00:03:17.240
but for a given number of bits say four

76
00:03:17.240 --> 00:03:20.460
a classical computer can take on any of the

77
00:03:20.460 --> 00:03:24.700
two to the four or sixteen possible states

78
00:03:24.700 --> 00:03:28.660
a quantum computer can also access sixteen possible states

79
00:03:28.660 --> 00:03:31.420
but it can exist in a super position of all

80
00:03:31.420 --> 00:03:34.099
