81
00:03:34.100 --> 00:03:38.700
and operations can be performed on this entire superposition

82
00:03:38.700 --> 00:03:40.700
for four cubits this may not seem

83
00:03:40.700 --> 00:03:43.400
like such a big deal but imagine what could be done with

84
00:03:43.400 --> 00:03:45.940
a quantum computer in two to the twenty or

85
00:03:45.940 --> 00:03:47.800
two to the one hundred and twenty seven

86
00:03:47.800 --> 00:03:51.520
states simultaneously there are many other differences

87
00:03:51.520 --> 00:03:53.980
between classical and quantity computing that will

88
00:03:53.980 --> 00:03:55.979
all play a role in this subject

89
00:03:55.980 --> 00:03:59.560
quantum states have complex probability amplitudes

90
00:03:59.560 --> 00:04:02.280
manipulations of quantum systems are carried out with

